"title": "8463: priority, of faith, hope and love",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8463",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Putting God first--living according to his word--serves the glory of God and also the best interests of believers, by giving them true wisdom for daily living.</p>\n<h2>The wisdom of making faith a priority</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:6\">HEB 11:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Putting the fear of God before other considerations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:19\">PSA 31:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:17\">EXO 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:15\">NEH 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:7\">PRO 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Preferring God's way to sinful advice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1-Ps1:2\">PSA 1:1–1:2</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:13-Prov3:14\">PRO 3:13–3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:19\">PRO 8:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:32\">PRO 8:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:16\">NUM 31:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:28\">1KI 12:28</a></p>\n<h3>Choosing imaginative action rather than laziness or fearfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:30\">NUM 13:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:33\">1SA 25:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:16\">EPH 5:16</a>MAT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph25:10\">25:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:26-Matt25:27\">MAT 25:26–25:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:44-Matt25:45\">MAT 25:44–25:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:40\">MAT 26:40</a></p>\n<h3>Patient waiting rather than impetuous action</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:1\">PSA 40:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:14\">PSA 27:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:5-Ps37:6\">PSA 37:5–37:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:5\">PSA 62:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps123:2\">PSA 123:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:5-Prov3:6\">PRO 3:5–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:31\">ISA 40:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:6\">HOS 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:4-John2:5\">JHN 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:10\">REV 2:10</a></p>\n<h2>The wisdom of making hope a priority</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:19\">HEB 6:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:10-Ps147:11\">PSA 147:10–147:11</a></p>\n<h3>Putting true riches above earthly wealth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:9\">LUK 16:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:8\">DEU 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:24\">MAT 6:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21\">MAT 19:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:22\">LUK 18:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:29\">MAT 19:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:29-Mark10:30\">MRK 10:29–10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:29-Luke18:30\">LUK 18:29–18:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:26\">HEB 11:26</a></p>\n<h3>Putting eternal joy before temporal hardship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:17-2Cor4:18\">2CO 4:17–4:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:22\">ACT 14:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:18\">ROM 8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:10\">2TI 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:34\">HEB 10:34</a></p>\n<h2>The wisdom of making love a priority</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:13\">1CO 13:13</a></strong> <em>Paul's concern that love, rather than competition over spiritual gifts, should be made a priority.</em></p>\n<h3>Loyalty rather than opportunism</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:24\">PRO 18:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:16\">RUT 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:10\">2TI 4:10</a> <em>Demas' love for this world rather than loyalty</em></p>\n<h3>Following the Spirit rather than sinful human nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16\">GAL 5:16</a></strong> <em>Merely “human” activity betrays a failure of love for God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:10-Ps147:11\">PSA 147:10–147:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1-Isa31:3\">ISA 31:1–31:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5\">ROM 8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Inner sincerity rather than outward appearance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:9\">ROM 12:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:5\">EPH 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:22\">COL 3:22</a></p>\n<h3>Actions rather than mere words</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:18\">JAS 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:21-Matt7:22\">MAT 7:21–7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:18\">1JN 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Peace rather than disharmony</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:18\">ROM 12:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:19\">ROM 14:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:14\">HEB 12:14</a></p>\n<h3>Truth rather than falsehood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:19\">PRO 12:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:4\">ACT 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:9\">COL 3:9</a></p>",
